            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "from https://github.com/wez/wezterm/issues/2112#issuecomment-1155421350 : \r\n\r\n> It seems like Neovim uses the value of `TERM` instead of checking terminfo caps for this.\r\n\r\nFor setting title the only condition we check is here: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/c4f3d41d6b06f3a8b399a36d7f3def8f25a71208/src/nvim/tui/tui.c#L1432\r\n\r\nhowever, we _do_ have workarounds to patch `unibi_to_status_line` if it's not present in  terminfo: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/c4f3d41d6b06f3a8b399a36d7f3def8f25a71208/src/nvim/tui/tui.c#L1796-L1807\r\n\r\nso I think the answer to \"what does nvim look for in terminfo\" is this capability: \r\n\r\n    \"tsl\"     , \"to_status_line\"\r\n\r\nhowever we usually just fill that in as `\\x1b]0;` and perhaps should do that more aggressively.",
