            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I'm experiencing this same problem using PowerShell to open nvim inside Windows Terminal. The `TERM` environment variable is not set, and `:set title` has no effect. To work around the problem, I manually set `TERM` to `xterm-256color`. Now it works perfectly.\r\n\r\nIf any Windows users happen to stumble on this and wonder how to set environment variables inside Windows Terminal, go to settings and select the \"Windows PowerShell\" profile. Change the command line to `%SystemRoot%\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1.0\\powershell.exe -NoExit -Command \"& {$env:TERM = \\\"xterm-256color\\\"}`\r\n\r\nAlternatively, execute `notepad $PROFILE` in PowerShell and insert the following line in your profile (creating it if necessary):\r\n```powershell\r\n$env:TERM = \"xterm-256color\"\r\n```",
