            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> the same occurs with `foot`\r\n\r\nIf [this is the man page](https://man.archlinux.org/man/foot.1.en), you might be able to work around the problem by setting `TERM` to `xterm-256color` with command line arguments:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nfoot --term=\"xterm-256color\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt apparently sets `TERM` to `foot` by default, which neovim probably doesn't recognize yet.",
